      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): add delivery route lease store for isolated cron announce context",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #92460.\n\nReplaces the previously rejected approach from PR #92580. Instead of persisting the resolved delivery target onto the isolated cron session entry (which created a lifecycle leak — route data accumulated with no retirement hook), this PR introduces a **generic in-memory delivery route lease store** that:\n\n1. **Creates a lease** when `prepareCronRunContext` resolves the delivery target\n2. **Provides fallback lookup** in `resolveAnnounceOrigin` when the session entry lacks `deliveryContext`\n3. **Retires the lease** best-effort after `dispatchCronDelivery` completes\n4. **Automatically GCs** stale leases via TTL (1h default) and 2000-entry cap\n\nThis matches the maintainer's requested design (@vincentkoc in PR #92580 review):\n> \"The canonical fix needs a generic requester-route lease owned by the shared background-task completion/delivery lifecycle, separate from generic session identity, with retirement after final delivery settles.\"\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`src/infra/delivery-lease-store.ts`** (NEW): In-memory lease store — `registerDeliveryLease` / `lookupDeliveryLease` / `retireDeliveryLease` with TTL pruning and 2000-entry cap, following the existing `COMPLETED_DIRECT_CRON_DELIVERIES` pattern\n- **`src/agents/subagent-announce-origin.ts`**: `resolveAnnounceOrigin` gains optional `sessionKey` parameter; falls back to lease store when session entry has no `deliveryContext`\n- **`src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts`**: Register lease in `prepareCronRunContext` after delivery resolution; retire in `finalizeCronRun` after delivery dispatch (both normal and fatal-error paths)\n- **`src/agents/subagent-announce.ts`**: Pass `targetRequesterSessionKey` to `resolveAnnounceOrigin`\n- **`src/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-task-runtime.ts`**: Pass `requesterSessionKey` to `resolveAnnounceOrigin`\n- **`src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts`** (NEW): 8 unit tests covering register/lookup/TTL/prune/cap/retire/reset\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Isolated cron jobs with explicit `delivery.channel` now successfully route subagent announce completions through the delivery lease store, without persisting routing state onto the session entry.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64, Node v22.19.0, local OpenClaw source checkout.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `pnpm test src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts --run --reporter=verbose`\n  - `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts --run`\n  - `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce.test.ts --run`\n  - `pnpm test src/cron/isolated-agent/ --run`\n  - `pnpm build`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  Terminal output from lease store unit tests:\n  ```text\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > register and lookup > returns the registered context for the session key\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > register and lookup > overwrites an existing lease on re-registration\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > lookup returns undefined > for an unknown session key\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > lookup returns undefined > after explicit retirement\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > retire > is idempotent\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > retire > removes only the targeted key\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > prune and cap > evicts oldest entries when cap is exceeded\n  ✓ |unit-fast| src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts > reset > clears all leases\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n  Tests  8 passed (8)\n  ```\n  Subagent announce delivery tests: 97 passed\n  Subagent announce tests: 10 passed\n  All 352 cron isolated agent tests pass\n  `pnpm build` — exit 0\n- **Observed result after fix**: The delivery lease is created during cron run preparation, available for subagent announce origin resolution, and retired after delivery dispatch. Stale leases are automatically cleaned up by TTL-based GC with a 2000-entry safety cap.\n- **What was not tested**: Live webchat delivery roundtrip; the proof covers the session-state propagation and lease lifecycle paths that the bug report identifies, matching the same scope as PR #92580's proven coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/infra/delivery-lease-store.test.ts --run` — 8 passed\n- `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts --run` — 97 passed\n- `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce.test.ts --run` — 10 passed\n- `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-orphan-recovery.test.ts --run` — 25 passed\n- `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce.timeout.test.ts --run` — 10 passed\n- `pnpm test src/cron/isolated-agent/ --run` — 352 passed\n- `pnpm build` — exit 0\n\n@vincentkoc — this revision follows the design requested in your review of PR #92580. The delivery route is now held in a generic in-memory lease store (separate from session identity) with TTL-based GC and best-effort explicit retirement after delivery dispatch. Please re-review.",
